<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xml:lang="en"><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.3.4">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://yltafsm.github.io/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml"/><link href="https://yltafsm.github.io/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" hreflang="en"/><updated>2025-01-08T08:58:43+00:00</updated><id>https://yltafsm.github.io/feed.xml</id><title type="html">刘洋 Yang Liu</title><entry><title type="html">International Energy Agency (IEA) 15MW wind turbine</title><link href="https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2025/IEA15mw/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="International Energy Agency (IEA) 15MW wind turbine"/><published>2025-01-04T12:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-01-04T12:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2025/IEA15mw</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2025/IEA15mw/"><![CDATA[<p>The wind turbine model design is based on the IEA Wind 15-Megawatt offshore reference wind turbine. Definition of the IEA wind15-megawatt offshore reference wind turbine can be found <a href="https://www.nrel.gov/docs/fy20osti/75698.pdf">here</a>. We made slightly modifications to the original design which is reported in the table below.</p> <table> <thead> <tr> <th style="text-align: left">Name</th> <th style="text-align: center">Our model</th> </tr> </thead> <tbody> <tr> <td style="text-align: left">Rotor diameter</td> <td style="text-align: center">\(\mathbf{240~\mathrm{m}}\)</td> </tr> <tr> <td style="text-align: left">Blade length</td> <td style="text-align: center">\(\mathbf{117~\mathrm{m}}\)</td> </tr> <tr> <td style="text-align: left">Hub diameter</td> <td style="text-align: center">\(\mathbf{3.97~\mathrm{m}}\)</td> </tr> <tr> <td style="text-align: left">Nacelle radius</td> <td style="text-align: center">\(\mathbf{3.97~\mathrm{m}}\)</td> </tr> <tr> <td style="text-align: left">Precone</td> <td style="text-align: center">\(\mathbf{0}^\circ\)</td> </tr> <tr> <td style="text-align: left">Shaft tilt</td> <td style="text-align: center">\(\mathbf{0}^\circ\)</td> </tr> <tr> <td style="text-align: left">Blade prebend</td> <td style="text-align: center">\(\mathbf{4~\mathrm{m}}\)</td> </tr> <tr> <td style="text-align: left">Wind tower height</td> <td style="text-align: center">\(\mathbf{150~\mathrm{m}}\)</td> </tr> <tr> <td style="text-align: left">Wind tower top diameter</td> <td style="text-align: center">\(\mathbf{5~\mathrm{m}}\)</td> </tr> <tr> <td style="text-align: left">Wind tower base diameter</td> <td style="text-align: center">\(\mathbf{10~\mathrm{m}}\)</td> </tr> <tr> <td style="text-align: left">Rated rotational speed</td> <td style="text-align: center">\(\mathbf{7.55~\mathrm{rpm}}\)</td> </tr> <tr> <td style="text-align: left">Wind speed</td> <td style="text-align: center">\(\mathbf{10.59~\mathrm{m/s}}\)</td> </tr> <tr> <td style="text-align: left">Tip speed</td> <td style="text-align: center">\(\mathbf{95~\mathrm{m/s}}\)</td> </tr> </tbody> </table> <div class="row mt-3 justify-content-center"> <div class="col-sm-3 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://openfast.readthedocs.io/en/dev/_images/aerodyn_driver_geom-480.webp 480w,https://openfast.readthedocs.io/en/dev/_images/aerodyn_driver_geom-800.webp 800w,https://openfast.readthedocs.io/en/dev/_images/aerodyn_driver_geom-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://openfast.readthedocs.io/en/dev/_images/aerodyn_driver_geom.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> <figcaption>Definition of basic turbine geometry</figcaption> </div> </div> <h1 id="comparison-of-5mw-left-and-15-mw-right">Comparison of 5MW (left) and 15 MW (right)</h1> <div class="row mt-3 justify-content-center"> <div class="col-sm-6 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/15mw/15mw_5mw.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls="" loop=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="row mt-3 justify-content-center"> <div class="col-sm-4 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-domain-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-domain-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-domain-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-domain.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm-4 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-SI2-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-SI2-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-SI2-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-SI2.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="row mt-3 justify-content-center"> <div class="col-sm-4 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-SI1-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-SI1-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-SI1-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-SI1.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <p>Computational Domain (<em>left</em>). The origin of the computational domain is located at the center of wind turbine hub. The inflow, outflow, lateral, top, and bottom boundary is approximately \(1.5R\), \(2R\), \(2R\), \(2R\), \(1.25R\) away from the computation center. Mesh structure around the rotor (<em>right</em>), blade SIs (<em>green</em>) and the rotor SI (<em>gray</em>), and wind turbine blades (<em>blue</em>).</p> <div class="row mt-3 justify-content-center"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-blade-surface-mesh-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-blade-surface-mesh-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-blade-surface-mesh-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-blade-surface-mesh.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <p>Blade surface mesh</p> <div class="row mt-3 justify-content-center"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-blade-sections-mesh-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-blade-sections-mesh-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-blade-sections-mesh-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-blade-sections-mesh.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <p>Cross-section mesh inside the blade SI at approximately \(0.1R\) to \(0.95R\).</p> <div class="row mt-3 justify-content-center"> <div class="col-sm-4 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-x0-mesh-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-x0-mesh-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-x0-mesh-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-x0-mesh.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="row mt-3 justify-content-center"> <div class="col-sm-4 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-y0-mesh-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-y0-mesh-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-y0-mesh-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-y0-mesh.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="row mt-3 justify-content-center"> <div class="col-sm-4 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-SI1-mesh-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-SI1-mesh-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-SI1-mesh-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-SI1-mesh.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <p>Cross-sections of the mesh at \(x_2 = 0\) (<em>top</em>), \(x_1= 0\) (<em>middle</em>), and mesh on the inner surface of the rotor SI and the tower surface (<em>bottom</em>). The checkerboard pattern NURBS elements.</p> <div class="row mt-3 justify-content-center"> <div class="col-sm-6 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/15mw/15mw_vortex.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls="" loop=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <p>Isosurfaces corresponding to a positive value of the second invariant of the velocity gradient tensor, colored by the velocity magnitude, at 0.17 and 0.33 turbine rotation period.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm-4 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-power-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-power-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-power-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-power.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm-4 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-thrust-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-thrust-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-thrust-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-thrust.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <p>Power generated by the rotor (<em>left</em>). Thrust acting on the wind turbine (<em>right</em>).</p> <div class="row mt-3 justify-content-center"> <div class="col-sm-6 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-reference-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-reference-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-reference-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-reference.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <p>Reference Value from <a href="https://www.nrel.gov/docs/fy20osti/75698.pdf">IEA official document</a>. uid rounded z-depth-1” zoomable=true %} &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; Power generated by the rotor (<em>left</em>). Thrust acting on the wind turbine (<em>right</em>).</p> <div class="row mt-3 justify-content-center"> <div class="col-sm-6 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-reference-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-reference-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-reference-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/15mw/15mw-reference.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <p>Reference Value from <a href="https://www.nrel.gov/docs/fy20osti/75698.pdf">IEA official document</a>.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="ST-SI"/><category term="IGA"/><category term="wind-turbine"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Flow analysis of IEA 15MW wind turbine]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Above the sky</title><link href="https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/helicopter-video/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Above the sky"/><published>2024-12-11T12:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-12-11T12:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/helicopter-video</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/helicopter-video/"><![CDATA[<p>One framework, endless possibilities.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/MOVIE/HELICOPTER/helicopter_above_sky.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="caption"> Isogeometric Analysis of a helicopter in forward flight </div> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/helicopter/202311-hover.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="caption"> Isosurface corresponding to a positive value of the second invariant of the velocity gradient tensor. Colored by velocity magnitude </div> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm-4 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/helicopter/202307-rotor.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm-4 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/helicopter/202307-blades.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm-4 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/helicopter/202307-blade-onboard.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="caption"> Helicopter cyclic control </div> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm-6 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/helicopter/202310-body.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm-6 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/helicopter/202311-mesh.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <div class="caption"> Helicopter body and its surface moving mesh </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="ST-SI"/><category term="ST-VMS"/><category term="IGA"/><category term="helicopter"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[State-of-the-art helicopter computation]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Computation Methods for Wind Farm Scale Isogeometric Analysis</title><link href="https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/5mw-farm/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Computation Methods for Wind Farm Scale Isogeometric Analysis"/><published>2024-12-02T07:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-12-02T07:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/5mw-farm</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/5mw-farm/"><![CDATA[<img-comparison-slider> <figure slot="first"> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/checker_x1-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/checker_x1-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/checker_x1-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/checker_x1.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> <figure slot="second"> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/checker2_x1-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/checker2_x1-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/checker2_x1-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/checker2_x1.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </img-comparison-slider> <p>The key idea is to model the boundary condition at the pink surface, which can be displayed by toggling the slider bar.</p> <img-comparison-slider> <figure slot="first"> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/farm-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/farm-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/farm-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/farm.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> <figure slot="second"> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/farm0-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/farm0-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/farm0-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/farm0.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </img-comparison-slider> <p>“The concept of the ‘Extended-Domain Method (EDM)’ combined with the ‘Carrier-Domain Method (CDM)’ for high-resolution, blade-resolved wind farm computations.”</p> <img-comparison-slider> <figure slot="first"> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/farm3-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/farm3-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/farm3-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/farm3.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> <figure slot="second"> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/farm4-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/farm4-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/farm4-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/farm4.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </img-comparison-slider> <p>“This is just a repeat of of single wind turbine computation.”</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="MDM"/><category term="CDM"/><category term="ST-Method"/><category term="ST-SUPS"/><category term="ST-VMS"/><category term="ST-SI"/><category term="IGA"/><category term="wind-farm"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Some ideas for blade resolved wind farm computation]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Multi-Domain Computation of the Wind Turbine Long-Wake Flow</title><link href="https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/5mw-wake/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Multi-Domain Computation of the Wind Turbine Long-Wake Flow"/><published>2024-12-01T07:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-12-01T07:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/5mw-wake</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/5mw-wake/"><![CDATA[<img-comparison-slider> <figure slot="first"> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/MDMW-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/MDMW-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/MDMW-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/MDMW.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> <figure slot="second"> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/MDMB-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/MDMB-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/MDMB-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/MDMB.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </img-comparison-slider> <p>The Multi-Domain Method (<a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0045782598003053?via%3Dihub">MDM</a>), introduced 26 years ago, originally intended for cost-effective computation of long-wake flows and later extended in scope to cover additional classes of flow problems. We take full advantage of this method in the long-wake flow computation of NREL 5MW wind Turbine.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="MDM"/><category term="ST-VMS"/><category term="IGA"/><category term="wake-flow"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Multi-Domain Method]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">NREL 5MW Wind Turbine Short Wake Flow</title><link href="https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/nrel5mw/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="NREL 5MW Wind Turbine Short Wake Flow"/><published>2024-11-25T12:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-11-25T12:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/nrel5mw</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/nrel5mw/"><![CDATA[<img-comparison-slider> <figure slot="first"> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/STSIW1-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/STSIW1-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/STSIW1-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/STSIW1.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> <figure slot="second"> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/STSIB1-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/STSIB1-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/STSIB1-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/5mw/STSIB1.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </img-comparison-slider> <p>Isogeometric Analysis of NREL 5MW offshore wind turbine.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="ST-VMS"/><category term="ST-SI"/><category term="IGA"/><category term="wind-turbine"/><category term="wake-flow"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Isogeometric Analysis of NREL 5MW offshore wind turbine]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Isogeometric Analysis of a Helicopter with Main and Tail rotor</title><link href="https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/heli-iga/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Isogeometric Analysis of a Helicopter with Main and Tail rotor"/><published>2024-11-23T13:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-11-23T13:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/heli-iga</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/heli-iga/"><![CDATA[<div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/IGA/202311-rotor-zoom-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/IGA/202311-rotor-zoom-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/IGA/202311-rotor-zoom-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/IGA/202311-rotor-zoom.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/IGA/202311-rotor-side-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/IGA/202311-rotor-side-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/IGA/202311-rotor-side-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/IGA/202311-rotor-side.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <p>With a double-swept design, the tip of the helicopter blade experiences weaker blade-vortex interaction compared to that of a ‘straight’ blade</p> <div class="row mt-3 justify-content-center"> <div class="col-sm-10 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/helicopter/202311-hover.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <p>A rotated camera view of the vortices generated by the helicopter’s main rotor and tail rotor, providing a dynamic perspective of the vortex patterns and their interaction with the blade.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="ST-VMS"/><category term="ST-SI"/><category term="IGA"/><category term="helicopter"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Isogeometric Analysis of a Helicopter]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Mesh Moving for Helicopter’s Pitch, Yaw, and Roll Movement</title><link href="https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/heli-mesh-moving/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Mesh Moving for Helicopter’s Pitch, Yaw, and Roll Movement"/><published>2024-11-22T13:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-11-22T13:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/heli-mesh-moving</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/heli-mesh-moving/"><![CDATA[<div class="row mt-3 justify-content-center"> <div class="col-sm-6 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/helicopter/202310-body.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <p>Helicopter in hover state.</p> <div class="row mt-3 justify-content-center"> <div class="col-sm-6 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/helicopter/mesh-moving/ball_pitch.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="row mt-3 justify-content-center"> <div class="col-sm-6 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/helicopter/mesh-moving/ball_yaw.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="row mt-3 justify-content-center"> <div class="col-sm-6 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/helicopter/mesh-moving/ball_roll.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <p>Mesh moving for helicopter pitch, yaw, and roll movement</p> <div class="row mt-3 justify-content-center"> <div class="col-sm-6 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/helicopter/202311-mesh.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <p>Surface mesh for helicopter body, main rotor and tail rotor.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="ST-SI"/><category term="helicopter"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Mesh moving method]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Helicopter Model and Computational Domain</title><link href="https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/heli-model/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Helicopter Model and Computational Domain"/><published>2024-11-22T12:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-11-22T12:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/heli-model</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/heli-model/"><![CDATA[<p>The model is purchased from <a href="https://3dmodels.org/3d-models/airbus-helicopters-h160/#reviews">3dmodel.org</a>.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/HeliGeometry/heliblade-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/HeliGeometry/heliblade-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/HeliGeometry/heliblade-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/HeliGeometry/heliblade.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/HeliGeometry/helicopter-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/HeliGeometry/helicopter-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/HeliGeometry/helicopter-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/HeliGeometry/helicopter.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="caption"> Helicopter Model </div> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/HeliGeometry/helirotor-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/HeliGeometry/helirotor-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/HeliGeometry/helirotor-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/HeliGeometry/helirotor.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/HeliGeometry/heliball-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/HeliGeometry/heliball-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/HeliGeometry/heliball-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/HeliGeometry/heliball.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/HeliGeometry/helifuture-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/HeliGeometry/helifuture-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/HeliGeometry/helifuture-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/helicopters/HeliGeometry/helifuture.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <p>Computational domain. Slip interface (SI) for high-resolution mesh representation of boundary layer (<em>Green</em>), and SI for rotor and helicopter motion (<em>Transparent</em>)</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/helicopter/202307-blade-onboard.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/helicopter/202307-blades.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/helicopter/202307-rotor.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm-6 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/helicopter/202311-mesh.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <p>Cyclic control. The videos show pitch angle changes at different azimuth angles during one rotation.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="helicopter"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A toy helicopter model]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">紙飛行機</title><link href="https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/paper-airplane/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="紙飛行機"/><published>2024-09-10T12:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-09-10T12:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/paper-airplane</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/paper-airplane/"><![CDATA[<div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/kamihikouki/computational-domain-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/kamihikouki/computational-domain-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/kamihikouki/computational-domain-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/kamihikouki/computational-domain.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <p>The computational domain consists of two key regions designed to enhance simulation accuracy and accommodate the movement of the paper airplane. The inner region is a cube that encloses the paper airplane, serving as a mesh refinement zone to ensure high-resolution computations in the vicinity of the object. Surrounding this cube is a spherical domain that also encloses the paper airplane. The sphere provides the spatial framework necessary for simulating its aerodynamic behavior, including pitch, yaw, and roll motions, by accounting for the unbounded nature of the surrounding fluid.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm-4 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/kamihikouki/kamihikouki-mesh-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/kamihikouki/kamihikouki-mesh-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/kamihikouki/kamihikouki-mesh-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/kamihikouki/kamihikouki-mesh.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm-4 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/kamihikouki/kamihikouki-mesh-y0-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/kamihikouki/kamihikouki-mesh-y0-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/kamihikouki/kamihikouki-mesh-y0-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/kamihikouki/kamihikouki-mesh-y0.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm-4 mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/kamihikouki/kamihikouki-mesh-zoom-480.webp 480w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/kamihikouki/kamihikouki-mesh-zoom-800.webp 800w,https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/kamihikouki/kamihikouki-mesh-zoom-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/images/kamihikouki/kamihikouki-mesh-zoom.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" data-zoomable="" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <p>The paper airplane in the computation is modeled with zero-thickness wings, body, and tail (<em>left</em>), while the boundary layer mesh (<em>right</em>) ensures accurate resolution of the flow near the surface.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/kamihikouki/kamihikouki-trans.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls="" loop=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <p>The computation is done with the <a href="https://www.jp.tafsm.org/en/method/space-time-slip-interface-st-si-method">Space–time Slip Interface Method</a>.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/kamihikouki/glide-low-initial-speed-fsi.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls="" loop=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <p>The paper airplane is launched at a relatively low initial speed, achieved by carefully controlling the length of the stretched rubber band. This mechanism ensures consistent and controlled launches for testing. During flight, the wings of the paper airplane exhibit flapping motion due to fluid–structure interaction, where aerodynamic forces from the airflow interact dynamically with the thin paper wings. It demonstrates a coupling between the paper airplane’s structure and fluid flow. The video capturing this process was taken in a laboratory environment to minimize external disturbances, allowing for accurate observation.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/kamihikouki/experiment-1.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls="" loop=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <p>This video was recorded at Waseda University’s <a href="https://www.yamashitasekkei.co.jp/project/story/04.php">Toyama Campus</a>, which is my favorite campus because of its distinctive architectural design. In this video, we observe the same aeroelastic behavior of the wing as seen in the first video, where the aerodynamic forces interact with the wing’s structure, causing oscillations that affect its stability. As the paper plane glides through the air, it quickly loses speed due to aerodynamic drag, leading to a rapid loss of lift. Eventually, the paper airplane enters a <a href="https://learntoflyblog.com/aerodynamics-spins/">spin</a> state, a phenomenon where one wing stalls before the other, causing the plane to rotate uncontrollably. This spin behavior is a critical aspect of understanding the limits of flight stability and control in low-speed regimes. I thought it is a good material for education.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="ST-SI"/><category term="IGA"/><category term="kamihikouki"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A Paper airplane simulation for high school education]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Computation Framework for Wind Turbines and Long-Wake Flows</title><link href="https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/5mw-double/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Computation Framework for Wind Turbines and Long-Wake Flows"/><published>2024-09-10T12:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-09-10T12:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/5mw-double</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://yltafsm.github.io/blog/2024/5mw-double/"><![CDATA[<p>The computation framework comprise of <a href="https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s00466-020-01910-5">Space–Time Variational Multiscale Method</a>(ST-VMS), <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/316455323_Space-Time_Slip_Interface_ST-SI_Method_and_Its_ST_Friends">Space–Time Slip Interface (ST-SI) Method</a>, <a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0045782598003053">Multi-Domain Method</a>, and the <a href="https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s00466-022-02230-6">Carrier-Domain Method</a>.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/cdm/5mw-10d-perspective.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls="" loop=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/cdm/5mw-10d-main.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls="" loop=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <p>NREL 5MW wind turbine long-wake up to 10 diameters downstream. Isosurfaces corresponding to a positive value of the second invariant of the velocity gradient tensor. The long-wake flow is computed using CDM-D, which significantly reduces the computational cost compared to directly computing the long-wake domain.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/cdm/5mw-double-perspective.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls="" loop=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="https://userdir.tafsm.org/~yliu/website/videos/cdm/5mw-double-main.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls="" loop=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <p>Two back-to-back NREL 5MW wind turbines. The long-wake flow up to 10 diameters downstream of the first wind turbine. Isosurfaces corresponding to a positive value of the second invariant of the velocity gradient tensor. The downstream wind turbine is fully merged in the wake.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="MDM"/><category term="CDM"/><category term="ST-VSM"/><category term="ST-SI"/><category term="IGA"/><category term="wind-turbine"/><category term="wake-flow"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A computation framework for wind turbines and long-wake flows]]></summary></entry></feed>